c-libs-in-elisp
===============

This repository demonstrates nelisp-cfront by compiling verbatim functions
from third-party C sources.  Components carry different licenses:

1. SQLite-derived material — PUBLIC DOMAIN
   - sqlite/sqlite-subset.c : the function bodies (everything below the
     "verbatim function bodies" marker) are copied UNMODIFIED from the SQLite
     3.39.3 amalgamation (sqlite3.c).
   - sqlite/sqlite-subset.pp.c : the preprocessed form of the above.
   - sqlite/sqlite-subset.el : a mechanical translation of the above, emitted
     by nelisp-cfront.
   SQLite is in the public domain: https://www.sqlite.org/copyright.html
   sha256(sqlite3.c, 3.39.3) =
     e4e75433871863a69b47eb374772ff769d0ab5714997a2e2123a4941bc4c60a6
   See sqlite/PROVENANCE.md for per-function source line numbers.

2. Original showcase harness — GPL-3.0-or-later
   Copyright (C) 2026 zawatton
   - the typedef/macro preamble at the top of sqlite/sqlite-subset.c
   - sqlite/driver.c
   - scripts/*.sh
   - Makefile, README.org, this NOTICE
   This matches the license of nelisp-cfront and nelisp.

nelisp-cfront and nelisp themselves are separate repositories and are not
vendored here; the scripts locate them via CFRONT_ROOT / NELISP_ROOT.
